local compass = peripheral.wrap("left")

local function turn()
    turtle.dig()
    turtle.turnLeft()
    turtle.dig()
    turtle.turnLeft()
    turtle.dig()
    turtle.turnLeft()
    turtle.dig()
end

local function face(start)
    local current = compass.getFacing()
    if current == start then return end
    local poles = { north=0, east=1, south=2, west=3 }
    local is = poles[start]
    local ic = poles[current]
    local d = math.abs(is - ic)
    if d == 2 then
        turtle.turnLeft()
        turtle.turnLeft()
    else
        local tA = d == 1 and turtle.turnRight or turtle.turnLeft
        local tB = d == 1 and turtle.turnLeft or turtle.turnRight
        if is > ic then
            tA()
        else
            tB()
        end
    end
end

local function writeFacing(f)
    fs.open("facing", "w")
    fs.write(f)
    fs.close()
end

local function up()
    while turtle.detectUp() do
        turtle.digUp()
        turtle.up()
        turn()
    end
end

local function down()
    local detect, data = turtle.inspectDown()
    while not detect or data.name ~= "minecraft:dirt" and data.name ~= "minecraft:grass_block" do
        turtle.digDown()
        turtle.down()
    end
end

local function initialSetup()
    if fs.exists("facing") then
        local detect, data = turtle.inspectDown()
        if detect and data.name == "minecraft:dirt" or data.name == "minecraft:grass_block" then
            turtle.turnLeft()
            detect, data = turtle.inspect()
            if detect and data.name == "minecraft:birch_sappling" then
                turtle.turnRight()
                if not turtle.detect() then
                    turtle.select(1)
                    turtle.place()
                    return
                end
            end
        end
        local file = fs.open("facing", "r")
        local facing = file.readAll()
        file.close()
        up()
        down()
        face(facing)
    end
end

initialSetup()
while true do
    local start_facing = compass.getFacing()
    writeFacing(start_facing)
    if not turtle.detect() then
        turtle.select(1)
        turtle.place()
    end
    if not turtle.compare() then
        turtle.dig()
        turtle.forward()
        up()
        down()
        face(start_facing)
        turtle.back()
        turtle.select(1)
        turtle.place()
    end
    sleep(2)
    turtle.turnLeft()
end

    def update_day_table1(self, item):
        month = item.text(0)

        # Connect to the database

        cursor = connection.cursor()

        # Fetch the day values for the selected month and year from the gl_data table
        cursor.execute("SELECT day, glucose, pulse FROM gl_data WHERE year = ? AND month = ?", (self.year_selector.currentText(), month))

        self.day_table.resizeColumnsToContents()

    def update_data(self, item):
        selected_row = item.row()
        selected_column = item.column()

        if selected_column != 1:  # Only update the Glucose column
            return

        day_item = self.day_table.item(selected_row, 0)
        glucose_item = self.day_table.item(selected_row, 1)

        if day_item is not None and glucose_item is not None:
            day = day_item.text()
            glucose = glucose_item.text()

            # Connect to the database
            connection = sqlite3.connect('miaglic.db')
            cursor = connection.cursor()

            # Update the glucose value in the gl_data table
            cursor.execute("UPDATE gl_data SET glucose = ? WHERE year = ? AND month = ? AND day = ?",
                           (glucose, self.year_selector.currentText(), self.month_tree.currentItem().text(0), day))
            connection.commit()
        
            # Close the cursor and connection
            cursor.close()
            connection.close()
       
    def initialize_year_table(self, year_dgv):
        # Clear the table
        year_dgv.clear()
        year_dgv.setRowCount(0)
        year_dgv.setColumnCount(3)
        year_dgv.setSelectionBehavior(QTableWidget.SelectRows)
        year_dgv.setSelectionMode(QTableWidget.SingleSelection)
        year_dgv.setEditTriggers(QTableWidget.NoEditTriggers)

        # Connect to the miaglic.db database
        connection = sqlite3.connect('miaglic.db')
        cursor = connection.cursor()

        # Fetch the distinct years, their average glucose values, and the number of records from the gl_data table
        cursor.execute("SELECT year, AVG(glucose), COUNT(*) FROM gl_data GROUP BY year")
        year_data = cursor.fetchall()

        # Populate the table with the years, average glucose, and number of records
        year_dgv.setRowCount(len(year_data))
        year_dgv.setHorizontalHeaderLabels(["Year", "Average Glucose", "Number of Records"])
        for row, (year, avg_glucose, num_records) in enumerate(year_data):
            year_item = QTableWidgetItem(year)
            avg_glucose_item = QTableWidgetItem(str(round(avg_glucose, 2)))
            num_records_item = QTableWidgetItem(str(num_records))
            year_dgv.setItem(row, 0, year_item)
            year_dgv.setItem(row, 1, avg_glucose_item)
            year_dgv.setItem(row, 2, num_records_item)
        header = year_dgv.horizontalHeader()
        header.setSectionResizeMode(QHeaderView.ResizeToContents)
        header.setSectionResizeMode(QtWidgets.QHeaderView.ResizeToContents)                    

        # Close the cursor and connection
        cursor.close()
        connection.close()

    def update_month_table(self, year_dgv, month_dgv):
        selected_year = year_dgv.selectedItems()[0].text()

        # Connect to the miaglic.db database
        connection = sqlite3.connect('miaglic.db')
        cursor = connection.cursor()

        # Fetch the distinct months and their average glucose values for the selected year from the gl_data table
        cursor.execute("SELECT month, AVG(glucose), COUNT(*) FROM gl_data WHERE year=? GROUP BY month", (selected_year,))
        month_data = cursor.fetchall()

        # Populate the table with the months, average glucose, and number of records
        month_dgv.clear()
        month_dgv.setRowCount(len(month_data))
        month_dgv.setColumnCount(3)
        month_dgv.setHorizontalHeaderLabels(["Month", "Average Glucose", "Number of Records"])
        month_dgv.setSelectionBehavior(QTableWidget.SelectRows)
        month_dgv.setSelectionMode(QTableWidget.SingleSelection)
        month_dgv.setEditTriggers(QTableWidget.NoEditTriggers)
        for row, (month, avg_glucose, num_records) in enumerate(month_data):
            month_item = QTableWidgetItem(month)
            avg_glucose_item = QTableWidgetItem(str(round(avg_glucose, 2)))
            num_records_item = QTableWidgetItem(str(num_records))
            month_dgv.setItem(row, 0, month_item)
            month_dgv.setItem(row, 1, avg_glucose_item)
            month_dgv.setItem(row, 2, num_records_item)
        header = month_dgv.horizontalHeader()
        header.setSectionResizeMode(QHeaderView.ResizeToContents)
        header.setSectionResizeMode(QtWidgets.QHeaderView.ResizeToContents)               

        # Close the cursor and connection
        cursor.close()
        connection.close()

    def update_day_table(self, year_dgv, month_dgv, day_dgv):
        selected_year = year_dgv.selectedItems()[0].text()
        selected_month = month_dgv.selectedItems()[0].text()

        # Connect to the miaglic.db database
        connection = sqlite3.connect('miaglic.db')
        cursor = connection.cursor()

        # Fetch the days and their average glucose values for the selected year and month from the gl_data table
        cursor.execute("SELECT day, AVG(glucose), pulse, systolic, diastolic FROM gl_data WHERE year=? AND month=? GROUP BY day ORDER BY day DESC",
                    (selected_year, selected_month))
        day_data = cursor.fetchall()
        day_column_names = [description[0] for description in cursor.description]

        # Populate the table with the days, average glucose, and additional data
        day_dgv.clear()
        day_dgv.setRowCount(len(day_data))
        day_dgv.setColumnCount(len(day_column_names))
        day_dgv.setHorizontalHeaderLabels(day_column_names)
        day_dgv.setSelectionBehavior(QTableWidget.SelectRows)
        day_dgv.setSelectionMode(QTableWidget.SingleSelection)
        day_dgv.setEditTriggers(QTableWidget.NoEditTriggers)

        for row, (day, avg_glucose, pulse, systolic, diastolic) in enumerate(day_data):
            day_item = QTableWidgetItem(str(day))
            avg_glucose_item = QTableWidgetItem(str(round(avg_glucose, 2)))
            pulse_item = QTableWidgetItem(str(pulse) if pulse else "")
            systolic_item = QTableWidgetItem(str(systolic) if systolic else "")
            diastolic_item = QTableWidgetItem(str(diastolic) if diastolic else "")
            # medicine_info_item = QTableWidgetItem(str(medicine_info) if medicine_info else "")

            day_dgv.setItem(row, 0, day_item)
            day_dgv.setItem(row, 1, avg_glucose_item)
            day_dgv.setItem(row, 2, pulse_item)
            day_dgv.setItem(row, 3, systolic_item)
            day_dgv.setItem(row, 4, diastolic_item)
            # day_dgv.setItem(row, 5, medicine_info_item)

        # Resize the header to fit the column names
        header = day_dgv.horizontalHeader()
        header.setSectionResizeMode(QHeaderView.ResizeToContents)
        header.setSectionResizeMode(QtWidgets.QHeaderView.ResizeToContents)

        # Close the cursor and connection
        cursor.close()
        connection.close()
        
        if len(selected_month) > 0:
            # selected_month = selected_index[0].data()
            # # Update the graph based on the selected month
            figure = self.plot_graph(selected_month,selected_year)            
            self.update_graph(selected_month,selected_year,figure)               
           
    def set_table_style(self, table_widget, width=None):
        # Set table properties
        table_widget.setAlternatingRowColors(True)
        table_widget.verticalHeader().setDefaultSectionSize(20)
        table_widget.verticalHeader().setVisible(False)

        # Set font style for headers
        font = QFont()
        font.setBold(True)
        font.setPointSize(6)
        table_widget.horizontalHeader().setFont(font)

        # Set header background and text color
        header_style = """
            QHeaderView::section {{
                background-color: #EEEEEE;
                color: #333333;
            }}
        """
        table_widget.horizontalHeader().setStyleSheet(header_style)

        # Set table background color
        table_style = """
            QTableWidget {{
                background-color: #FFFFFF;
                border: none;
                selection-background-color: #B5D5FF;
            }}
        """
        table_widget.setStyleSheet(table_style)

        # Set table width if specified
        if width is not None:
            table_widget.setMaximumWidth(width)

        # Resize row header to fill description
        table_widget.resizeRowsToContents()
        # Resize the header to fit the column names
        header = table_widget.horizontalHeader()
        header.setSectionResizeMode(QHeaderView.ResizeToContents)
        header = table_widget.verticalHeader()
        header.setSectionResizeMode(QHeaderView.ResizeToContents)
        
    def set_panel_style(self, panel_widget, expand=False):
        # Set panel properties
        panel_widget.setStyleSheet("background-color: #FFFFFF; border: none;")

        # Set font style for headers
        font = QFont()
        font.setBold(True)
        font.setPointSize(8)
        header = panel_widget.layout().itemAt(0).widget().horizontalHeader()
        header.setFont(font)

        # Set header background and text color
        header_style = """
            QHeaderView::section {{
                background-color: #EEEEEE;
                color: #333333;
            }}
        """
        header.setStyleSheet(header_style)

        # Expand panel if specified
        if expand:
            panel_widget.setSizePolicy(
                QSizePolicy.Expanding,
                QSizePolicy.Expanding
            )
        
    def resize_to_75_percent(self):
        screen = QGuiApplication.primaryScreen()
        screen_geometry = screen.geometry()
        width = int(screen_geometry.width() * 0.75)
        height = int(screen_geometry.height() * 0.75)
        self.setGeometry(
            screen_geometry.center().x() - width // 2,
            screen_geometry.center().y() - height // 2,
            width, height
        )   
            
    def center_on_screen(self):
        # Get the primary screen
        screen = QGuiApplication.primaryScreen()
        if screen is not None:
            # Get the screen's geometry
            screen_geometry = screen.geometry()

            # Calculate the center point
            center_x = screen_geometry.center().x()
            center_y = screen_geometry.center().y()

            # Calculate the position for the top-left corner of the form
            form_width = self.frameGeometry().width()
            form_height = self.frameGeometry().height()
            form_x = center_x - form_width // 2
            form_y = center_y - form_height // 2

            # Move the form to the center of the screen
            self.move(form_x, form_y)

    def plot_graph(self,selected_month,selected_year):
        if len(selected_month) == 0:
            return        
        # Execute the query to retrieve the average glucose values
        # Retrieve the data from the gl_data table
        spy4me("DENTROPLOT", 1 )
        connection = sqlite3.connect("miaglic.db")
        self.cursor = connection.cursor()
        self.cursor.execute("SELECT glucose,day FROM gl_data WHERE year=? AND month=? GROUP BY day ORDER BY day DESC",
                    (selected_year, selected_month))
        results = self.cursor.fetchall()
        print(results)

        # Extract the average glucose values and dates from the results
        average_glucose_values = [row[0] for row in results]
        dates = [int(row[1]) for row in results]  # Convert dates to integers

        sns.lineplot(x=dates, y=average_glucose_values, marker='o')

        # Customize the plot
        plt.xlabel('AVG')
        plt.ylabel('DATE')
        plt.title('Average Glucose Values')
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)

        # Return the figure object
        return plt.gcf()
    def update_graph(self, selected_month, selected_year, figure):
        # Get the data for the selected month and update the graph accordingly
        dates, average_glucose_values = self.get_month_data(selected_month,selected_year)

        # Clear the previous plot

        # Set the figure object as the current figure

        # Customize the plot
        plt.xlabel("Day")
        plt.ylabel("Glucose Level")
        plt.title("Glucose Level Variation")
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.draw()

    def update_graph1(self, selected_month, selected_year, figure):
        # Get the data for the selected month and update the graph accordingly
        x, y = self.get_month_data(selected_month,selected_year)
        self.plot_graph(selected_month,selected_year)           

        # Clear the previous plot

        # Set the figure object as the current figure

        # Create the plot using Seaborn
        sns.lineplot(x=x, y=y)

        # Customize the plot
        plt.xlabel("Day")
        plt.ylabel("Glucose Level")
        plt.title("Glucose Level Variation")
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.draw()

    def get_month_data(self,selected_month,selected_year):
        # Connect to the miaglic.db database
        connection = sqlite3.connect('miaglic.db')
        cursor = connection.cursor()

        # Execute a query to retrieve the data for the selected month
        cursor.execute("SELECT day, AVG(glucose) FROM gl_data WHERE year=? AND month=? GROUP BY day ORDER BY day DESC",
                    (selected_year, selected_month))
        results = self.cursor.fetchall()
        month_data = cursor.fetchall()

        # Extract the day and glucose values from the results
        days = [row[0] for row in month_data]
        glucose_values = [row[1] for row in month_data]

        # Close the cursor and connection
        cursor.close()
        connection.close()

        return days, glucose_values

import os
import shutil
from tqdm import tqdm

def move_files_to_images_folder():
    current_path = os.getcwd()
    images_folder = os.path.join(current_path, "Imagens")
    if not os.path.exists(images_folder):
        os.makedirs(images_folder)

    files = os.listdir(current_path)
    image_files = [file for file in files if file.lower().endswith((".png", ".jpg", ".jpeg"))]

    for file in tqdm(image_files, desc="Movendo arquivos"):
        file_path = os.path.join(current_path, file)
        destination_path = os.path.join(images_folder, file)
        shutil.move(file_path, destination_path)

    print("Arquivos movidos com sucesso para a subpasta 'Imagens'.")

def move_files_to_icons_folder():
    current_path = os.getcwd()
    icons_folder = os.path.join(current_path, "Icones")
    if not os.path.exists(icons_folder):
        os.makedirs(icons_folder)

    files = os.listdir(current_path)
    icon_files = [file for file in files if file.lower().endswith(".ico")]

    for file in tqdm(icon_files, desc="Movendo arquivos"):
        file_path = os.path.join(current_path, file)
        destination_path = os.path.join(icons_folder, file)
        shutil.move(file_path, destination_path)

    print("Arquivos movidos com sucesso para a subpasta 'Icones'.")

def move_files_to_archives_folder():
    current_path = os.getcwd()
    archives_folder = os.path.join(current_path, "Compactados")
    if not os.path.exists(archives_folder):
        os.makedirs(archives_folder)

    files = os.listdir(current_path)
    archive_files = [file for file in files if file.lower().endswith((".zip", ".rar"))]

    for file in tqdm(archive_files, desc="Movendo arquivos"):
        file_path = os.path.join(current_path, file)
        destination_path = os.path.join(archives_folder, file)
        shutil.move(file_path, destination_path)

    print("Arquivos movidos com sucesso para a subpasta 'Compactados'.")

def move_files_to_videos_folder():
    current_path = os.getcwd()
    videos_folder = os.path.join(current_path, "Videos")
    if not os.path.exists(videos_folder):
        os.makedirs(videos_folder)

    files = os.listdir(current_path)
    video_files = [file for file in files if file.lower().endswith((".mp4", ".mkv", ".ts"))]

    for file in tqdm(video_files, desc="Movendo arquivos"):
        file_path = os.path.join(current_path, file)
        destination_path = os.path.join(videos_folder, file)
        shutil.move(file_path, destination_path)

    print("Arquivos movidos com sucesso para a subpasta 'Videos'.")

def move_files_to_texts_folder():
    current_path = os.getcwd()
    texts_folder = os.path.join(current_path, "Textos")
    if not os.path.exists(texts_folder):
        os.makedirs(texts_folder)

    files = os.listdir(current_path)
    text_files = [file for file in files if file.lower().endswith((".txt", ".doc"))]

    for file in tqdm(text_files, desc="Movendo arquivos"):
        file_path = os.path.join(current_path, file)
        destination_path = os.path.join(texts_folder, file)
        shutil.move(file_path, destination_path)

    print("Arquivos movidos com sucesso para a subpasta 'Textos'.")

def move_files_to_dvd_folder():
    current_path = os.getcwd()
    dvd_folder = os.path.join(current_path, "Filmes DVD-R")
    if not os.path.exists(dvd_folder):
        os.makedirs(dvd_folder)

    files = os.listdir(current_path)
    dvd_files = [file for file in files if file.lower().endswith(".iso")]

    for file in tqdm(dvd_files, desc="Movendo arquivos"):
        file_path = os.path.join(current_path, file)
        destination_path = os.path.join(dvd_folder, file)
        shutil.move(file_path, destination_path)

    print("Arquivos movidos com sucesso para a subpasta 'Filmes DVD-R'.")

def show_menu():
    print("1 - Mover extensão .png, .jpg, .jpeg")
    print("2 - Mover extensão .ico")
    print("3 - Mover extensão .zip, .rar")
    print("4 - Mover extensão .mp4, .mkv, .ts")
    print("5 - Mover extensão .txt, .doc")
    print("6 - Mover extensão .iso")
    print("7 - Sair")

def main():
    while True:
        show_menu()
        choice = input("Escolha uma opção: ")

        if choice == "1":
            move_files_to_images_folder()
        elif choice == "2":
            move_files_to_icons_folder()
        elif choice == "3":
            move_files_to_archives_folder()
        elif choice == "4":
            move_files_to_videos_folder()
        elif choice == "5":
            move_files_to_texts_folder()
        elif choice == "6":
            move_files_to_dvd_folder()
        elif choice == "7":
            break
        else:
            print("Opção inválida. Tente novamente.")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()

content:
--- Program : Item Filter System
--- Author : LightKnight51
--- Last modification : 23/06/2023

--- Utils API
local libraryName = "MarquitoLuaUtils"
local libraryCode = "mVTSwvw1"

-- Drop every items accepted down, and other up (it's for a item's trash)
function FilterItems(excludingItems)
    -- Array size
    local arraySize = table.getn(excludingItems)
    
    -- Loop each items inside the turtle
    for m = 1, 16  do
        local isAcceptedItem = true
        -- Get item name in current slot
        local turtleCurrentItemName = nil
        if turtle.getItemDetail(m) ~= nil then
            turtleCurrentItemName = turtle.getItemDetail(m).name
        end
        
        if turtleCurrentItemName ~= nil and arraySize ~= nil and arraySize > 0 then
            for s = 1, arraySize do
                if string.find(turtleCurrentItemName, excludingItems[s]) then
                    -- If the item in the slot match with an exluding item, we drop up
                    isAcceptedItem = false
                    break
                end
            end

            turtle.select(m)
            if isAcceptedItem then
                -- Item accepted
                turtle.dropDown()
            else
                -- Item refused
                turtle.dropUp()
            end
        end
    end
end

-- Initialize the item filter system
function InitItemFilterSystem()
    -- Set the ElevatorLevel from the conf
    local itemsString = tostring(MarquitoLuaUtils.GetConfValue("items_not_accepted"))

    if itemsString ~= nil and itemsString ~= "" then
        -- Array of items not accepted
        local items = MarquitoLuaUtils.Split(itemsString, ",")

        if MarquitoLuaUtils.IsAnArray(items) then
            while true do
                FilterItems(items)
                sleep(0.05)
            end
        end
    else
        MarquitoLuaUtils.SetConfValue("items_not_accepted", "")
    end
end

-- Download program
function DownloadProgram(pastebinCode, programName)
    if not fs.exists(programName) then
	    shell.run("pastebin get " .. pastebinCode .. " " .. programName)
    end
end

-- We need this library for other programs work
DownloadProgram(libraryCode, libraryName)
os.loadAPI("MarquitoLuaUtils")
-- Initialize the item filter system
InitItemFilterSystem()

import os
import time
import json
import sys

boletim = list()

open('initialization_data.txt', 'a')

def programa_boletim():
    os.system('cls')

    aluno = list()

    def mostrar_boletim():
        os.system('cls')
        print('\nSchool report:\n\n{}\n{}  {:50s}{:5s} {:5s} {:5s} {:5s}\n'.format('-' * 91, 'Nº', 'Name', 'Grade 1',
                                                                                      '  Grade 2', '  Grade 3',
                                                                                      '  Average'))
        for c in range(0, len(boletim)):
            print(
                '{}   {:50s}  {:>5}     {:>5}     {:>5}     {:>5}'.format(c+1, (boletim[c][0]).title(),
                                                                          boletim[c][1],
                                                                          boletim[c][2], boletim[c][3],
                                                                          boletim[c][4]))
        print('-' * 91)

    while True:
        os.system('cls')
        fechar_boletim = False

        inicio = input('\nType what you want to do:\n\n'
                       '1 - Add students\n'
                       '2 - Remove students\n'
                       '3 - Show scholl report\n\n'
                       'S - Save and exit\n\n\n'
                       '>>> ').lower()

        if inicio == '1':
            while fechar_boletim is False:
                os.system('cls')
                print('R - Return\n\nWhat do you want to add to the list?\n')

                nome = input('\nName: ').strip()

                if nome.lower() == 'r':
                    input(f'{mostrar_boletim()}\n\n PRESS ENTER TO GO BACK')
                    fechar_boletim = True

                else:
                    try:
                        not1 = float(input('Grade 1: '))
                        not2 = float(input('Grade 2: '))
                        not3 = float(input('Grade 3: '))

                        media = (not1 + not2 + not3) / 3

                        aluno.append(nome), aluno.append(str(round(not1, 1))), aluno.append(str(round(not2, 1))), \
                            aluno.append(str(round(not3, 1))), aluno.append(str(round(media, 1)))

                        boletim.append(aluno[:])
                        aluno.clear()

                        with open(f'{nome_arquivo}.json', 'w') as escrever:
                            json.dump(boletim, escrever)

                        global arquivo_encontrado
                        if arquivo_encontrado == False:
                            open('initialization_data.txt', 'a').write(nome_arquivo + '\n')
                            arquivo_encontrado = True

                        elif arquivo_encontrado == True:
                            continue

                    except ValueError:
                        aluno.clear()
                        print('Enter something valid!')
                        time.sleep(2)
                        continue

        elif inicio == '2':
            while fechar_boletim is False:
                if (boletim == []) is False:
                    print(f'{mostrar_boletim()}\n')
                    print('R - Return           C - Clear\n')
                    remover_item = input('>>> ')

                    if remover_item.isnumeric():
                        remover_item1 = int(remover_item)

                        if (remover_item1 - 1) < len(boletim) and not remover_item1 == 0:
                            del boletim[remover_item1 - 1]

                            with open(f'{nome_arquivo}.json', 'w') as escrever:
                                json.dump(boletim, escrever)

                        elif (remover_item1 - 1) > (len(boletim) - 1) or remover_item1 == 0:
                            print('There is no item with this number in the list!')
                            time.sleep(2)
                            os.system('cls')

                    else:
                        if (remover_item == 'r' or remover_item == 'R') is True:
                            fechar_boletim = True

                        elif (remover_item == 'c' or remover_item == 'C') is True:
                            boletim.clear()
                            input(f'{mostrar_boletim()}\n\nPRESS ENTER TO CONTINUE')
                            fechar_boletim = True

                        else:
                            print('Enter something valid')
                            time.sleep(2)

                elif (boletim == []) is True:
                    print('There are no more items to remove from the list!')
                    time.sleep(3)
                    fechar_boletim = True

        elif inicio == '3':
            input(f'{mostrar_boletim()}\n\nPRESS ENTER TO CONTINUE')

        elif inicio == 's':
            sys.exit()


while True:
    arquivo_encontrado = False
    voltar_menu = False
    os.system('cls')

    verificar_arquivo = input('\nWhat do you want to do?\n'
                              '\n1 - Open a saved file'
                              '\n2 - Create a new file\n'
                              '\nS - Save and exit the program\n\n\n>>> ').lower()

    if verificar_arquivo == '2':
        while True:
            os.system('cls')
            nome_arquivo = input('\nR - Return\n\nEnter the name of the new file\n\n>>> ').lower()
            
            if nome_arquivo == 'r':
                break

            confirmar = input(f'Do you want to create the file named "{nome_arquivo}"? [Y/N]\n\n>>> ').upper()
            
            if confirmar == 'Y':
                nome_arquivo = f'{nome_arquivo}'
                negativo = False

                with open('initialization_data.txt', 'r') as ler:
                    linhas = ler.readlines()

                    for linha in linhas:
                        if nome_arquivo in linha:
                            sobrescrever = input('Another file with the same name already exists\n'
                                                 'Do you want to overwrite it? [Y/N]\n\n>>> ').upper()

                            if sobrescrever == 'Y':
                                with open(f'{nome_arquivo}.json', 'w') as ler2:
                                    json.dump([], ler2)

                                with open(f'{nome_arquivo}.json', 'r') as ler2:
                                    boletim = json.load(ler2)

                                    arquivo_encontrado = True
                                    programa_boletim()

                            elif sobrescrever == 'N':
                                negativo = True
                                break

                        else:
                            continue

                    if negativo == True:
                        break
                    else:
                        programa_boletim()

            elif confirmar == 'N':
                continue

            else:
                print('Enter "Y" or "y" for yes and "N" or "n" for no.')
                time.sleep(3)

    elif verificar_arquivo == '1':
        while True:
            os.system('cls')

            nome_arquivo = input('\nr - Return\n\nEnter file name\n\n>>> ').lower()

            if nome_arquivo == 'r':
                break

            else:
                with open('initialization_data.txt', 'r') as ler:
                    linhas = ler.readlines()

                    for linha in linhas:
                        if nome_arquivo in linha:
                            try:
                                with open(f'{nome_arquivo}.json', 'r') as ler2:
                                    boletim = json.load(ler2)

                                    arquivo_encontrado = True
                                    programa_boletim()
                        
                            except FileNotFoundError:
                                print('\nThis file does not exist in the database.'
                                      '\nCheck the name or create a new file.')
                                time.sleep(2)

                        else:
                            continue

                    print('\nThis file does not exist in the database.'
                          '\nCheck the name or create a new file.')
                    time.sleep(2)

    elif verificar_arquivo == 's':
        break

content:
def convert_line_width_to_velocity(lineWidth, lineE):
    '''lineWidth and lineE can have any units.
    Returns velocity in units of km/s.'''
    return constants.c * (lineWidth/lineE) * 1e-03

velo = convert_line_width_to_velocity(lineWidth, lineE) # Velocity for gas in emission region
print(velo)
velo_max = convert_line_width_to_velocity(lineWidth + lineWidth_err + lineE_err, lineE) # Upper bound
print(velo_max)
velo_min = convert_line_width_to_velocity(lineWidth - lineWidth_err - lineE_err, lineE) # Lower bound
print(velo_min)
velo_err = velo_max - velo
print(velo_err)

title: Simple Noclip - Roblox
content:
-- use this in exector if u enjoy short text and the deafult values are good for you: --
--:: loadstring(game:HttpGet(("https://pastebin.com/raw/eSCiq7u3"),true))() ::--
local function make_msg(content: string)
	game.StarterGui:SetCore('SendNotification', {
		Title = 'Simple Noclip',
		Text = content,
		Duration = 7.5,
		Icon = 'http://www.roblox.com/asset/?id=13838346118'
	})
end

repeat wait() until game:IsLoaded() and game.Players.LocalPlayer

make_msg('Thanks for using my script!\n(made by @bloxxylenny on Discord).\nNumpad minus to fly down, numpad plus to fly up.')

local deafult_values = {
	["keybind"] = Enum.KeyCode.Insert,
	["ncspeed"] = 72,
}

local noclip_enabled = false

local player = game.Players.LocalPlayer

local uip = game:GetService('UserInputService')

local moveDown = false
local moveUp = false

uip.InputBegan:Connect(function(key, gpe)
	if not gpe then

		if key.KeyCode == deafult_values.keybind then

			noclip_enabled = not noclip_enabled
			
			local status = 'Enabled'
			
			if not noclip_enabled then
				status = 'Disabled'
			end
			
			local r: BasePart = player.Character:FindFirstChild('HumanoidRootPart')
			
			if r then
				r.Anchored = noclip_enabled
			end
			
			make_msg('Noclip: '..status)
		elseif key.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.KeypadMinus then
			moveDown = true
		elseif key.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.KeypadPlus then
			moveUp = true
		end
	end
end)

uip.InputEnded:Connect(function(key, gpe)
	if not gpe then
		
		if key.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.KeypadMinus then
			moveDown = false
		elseif key.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.KeypadPlus then
			moveUp = false
		end
	end
end)

game:GetService('RunService').RenderStepped:Connect(function(delta)
	local character = player.Character or player.CharacterAdded:Wait()
	
	if character then
		
		local root: BasePart = character:FindFirstChild('HumanoidRootPart')
		
		if root then
			if noclip_enabled then
				local humanoid: Humanoid = character:FindFirstChildWhichIsA('Humanoid')
				
				if humanoid then
					local cam = workspace.CurrentCamera
					root.Anchored = true
					
					local multiplier = 0
					
					if moveUp then
						multiplier += 1
					end
					
					if moveDown then
						multiplier -= 1
					end
					
					root.CFrame = CFrame.new(root.CFrame.Position + (cam.CFrame.YVector * multiplier * deafult_values.ncspeed * delta) + (humanoid.MoveDirection * deafult_values.ncspeed * delta)) * cam.CFrame.Rotation
				end
			end
		end
	end
end)

import pandas as pd
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer
from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline
from sklearn.impute import SimpleImputer
from sklearn.preprocessing import OneHotEncoder
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error


# ******************************************************************************************************
# ******************************************************************************************************
# 1. Read the 2 datasets and split the dataset - Choose 10 as maximum cardinality to drop some columns
# ******************************************************************************************************
# ******************************************************************************************************

# 1a. Read
X_full = pd.read_csv('../input/train.csv', index_col='Id')
X_test_full = pd.read_csv('../input/test.csv', index_col='Id')

# 1b. Remove rows with missing target, separate target from predictors
X_full.dropna(axis=0, subset=['SalePrice'], inplace=True)
y = X_full.SalePrice
X_full.drop(['SalePrice'], axis=1, inplace=True)

# 1c. Break off validation set from training data
X_train_full, X_valid_full, y_train, y_valid = train_test_split(X_full, y, train_size=0.8, test_size=0.2, random_state=0)

# 1d. Cardinality means the number of unique values in a column - OH Encoder is coming
categorical_cols = [cname for cname in X_train_full.columns if X_train_full[cname].nunique() < 10 and  X_train_full[cname].dtype == "object"]

# 1e. Select numerical columns
numerical_cols = [cname for cname in X_train_full.columns if X_train_full[cname].dtype in ['int64', 'float64']]

# 1f. Keep selected columns only
my_cols = categorical_cols + numerical_cols
X_train = X_train_full[my_cols].copy()
X_valid = X_valid_full[my_cols].copy()
X_test = X_test_full[my_cols].copy()

print(X_train.shape)
X_train.head()




# ******************************************************************************************************
# ******************************************************************************************************
# 2. Pipelines - Bundle a preprocessor and a model
# ******************************************************************************************************
# ******************************************************************************************************

# 2a. Preprocessing for numerical data
numerical_transformer = SimpleImputer(strategy='constant')

# 2b. Preprocessing for categorical data
categorical_transformer = Pipeline(steps=[('imputer', SimpleImputer(strategy='most_frequent')),
    ('onehot', OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown='ignore'))])

# 2c. Bundle preprocessing for numerical and categorical data into a preprocessor
preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(transformers=[
        ('num', numerical_transformer, numerical_cols),
        ('cat', categorical_transformer, categorical_cols)])

# 2d. Define model
model = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=100, random_state=0)

# 2e. Bundle preprocessing and modeling code in a pipeline
clf = Pipeline(steps=[('preprocessor', preprocessor), ('model', model)])

# 2f. Preprocessing of training data, fit model, preprocessing of validation data, make predictions
clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
preds = clf.predict(X_valid)
print('MAE:', mean_absolute_error(y_valid, preds))






# ******************************************************************************************************
# ******************************************************************************************************
# 3. Improve performance - One solution here is to change the SimpleImputer of numerical columns and model
# ******************************************************************************************************
# ******************************************************************************************************

# 3a. Preprocessing for numerical data
numerical_transformer = SimpleImputer()

# 3b. Preprocessing for categorical data
categorical_transformer = Pipeline(steps=[('imputer', SimpleImputer(strategy='most_frequent')),
	('onehot', OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown='ignore'))])

# 3c. Bundle preprocessing for numerical and categorical data
preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(transformers=[
        ('num', numerical_transformer, numerical_cols),
        ('cat', categorical_transformer, categorical_cols)])

# 3d. Define model
model = RandomForestRegressor()

# 3e. Bundle preprocessing and modeling code in a pipeline
my_pipeline = Pipeline(steps=[('preprocessor', preprocessor), ('model', model)])

# 3f. Preprocessing of training data, fit model, preprocessing of validation data, make predictions
my_pipeline.fit(X_train, y_train)
preds = my_pipeline.predict(X_valid)
score = mean_absolute_error(y_valid, preds)
print('MAE:', score)





# ******************************************************************************************************
# ******************************************************************************************************
# 4. Generate test predictions from the 2nd dataset using X_test
# ******************************************************************************************************
# ******************************************************************************************************

preds_test = my_pipeline.predict(X_test)
output = pd.DataFrame({'Id': X_test.index, 'SalePrice': preds_test})
output.to_csv('submission.csv', index=False)

title: Converter imagem em texto usando python em poucas linhas de código
content:
#Maiores detalhes como instalação em https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HHHkh9IOqhI

import pytesseract as pyt
import cv2

img = cv2.imread("text_img.png")

pyt.pytesseract.tesseract_cmd = "C:\\Program Files\\Tesseract-OCR\\tesseract.exe"

text = pyt.image_to_string(img)

print(text)
